      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:15:15",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) لَا أُصَلِّي عَلَى غَرِيقِ خَمْرٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Khalaf Bin Hammad, from Muhraz, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘I<sup>saww</sup> do not Pray over the one drowned in wine’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "15. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from Khalaf ibn Hammad from Muhriz from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, has said, ‘I do not perform Salat (prayer) on the dead body of one drowned in wine (a wine drinker).”’ "
        ]
      }
    },
